"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1933872-Olympics-2024-Ellie-Aldridge-Team-GB\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Team GB have finally landed a 13th gold medal at theParis Olympicsafter Ellie Aldridge claimed victory in the women's kitesurfing final.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 138, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 9, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9985898570030501, \"rank\": 0.001403968338352434, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sailing event was introduced at the Paris Games for the first time in Olympics history.\", \"from\": 139, \"to\": 230, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Aldridge clinched a silver medal at the Olympics test event last year.\", \"from\": 232, \"to\": 302, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 232, \"end\": 240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\", \"score\": 0.9117002513680444, \"rank\": 0.09667507335446503, \"text\": \"Aldridge\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But she upgraded the colour to gold after dominating her rivals at the Marseille Marina on Thursday.\", \"from\": 303, \"to\": 403, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 374, \"end\": 383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_de_Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9200874606956315, \"rank\": 0.0868531988463938, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_de_Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_de_Marseille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's Lauriane Nolot got her hands on the silver medal, while the Netherlands' Annelous Lammerts clinched the bronze.\", \"from\": 405, \"to\": 525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 405, \"end\": 411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.6183742603972998, \"rank\": 0.5905148869374663, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 474, \"end\": 485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.5545795625707546, \"rank\": 0.8031065919013114, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, USA's Daniela Moroz narrowly missed out on a medal after finishing fourth.\", \"from\": 526, \"to\": 611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 537, \"end\": 540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9890710630367217, \"rank\": 0.011043249051375896, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 543, \"end\": 550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Alves_Lima\", \"score\": 0.9926167743692237, \"rank\": 0.007430536555015969, \"text\": \"Daniela\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Alves_Lima\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Alves_Lima\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aldridge needed a total of three wins to take the gold medal but went into the final with only one victory to her name, while Nolot had two.\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 753, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 613, \"end\": 621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\", \"score\": 0.9117002513680444, \"rank\": 0.09667507335446503, \"text\": \"Aldridge\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldridge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Briton evened up the points by winning the first final race and stormed to her third win in the next one.\", \"from\": 754, \"to\": 867, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After the race had come to an end,BBCcommentator Niall Myant explained: \\\"Ellie Aldridge won that race - that was not gifted to her.\", \"from\": 869, \"to\": 1000, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 918, \"end\": 923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niall_of_the_Nine_Hostages\", \"score\": 0.9999881019533186, \"rank\": 1.1770055724597778e-05, \"text\": \"Niall\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niall_of_the_Nine_Hostages\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niall_of_the_Nine_Hostages\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was tenacious at that first windward mark rounding.\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1056, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She is celebrating in style.\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1087, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All of this being played out just in front of the beach here in Marseille.\", \"from\": 1088, \"to\": 1162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1152, \"end\": 1161, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_de_Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9200874606956315, \"rank\": 0.0868531988463938, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_de_Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_de_Marseille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Everybody up close to the action and what a performance she put on for everyone.\\\"\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1244, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:Coco Gauff rejected Carlos Alcaraz selfie but took snap with Nadal and Murray  And former sailing star Shirley Robertson, who won two Olympic gold medals, stated: \\\"It was flawless, wasn't it.\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1449, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1258, \"end\": 1268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Coco Gauff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\"}, {\"begin\": 1278, \"end\": 1292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\"}, {\"begin\": 1293, \"end\": 1299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selfie\", \"score\": 0.9999999981787369, \"rank\": 1.8212965022047095e-09, \"text\": \"selfie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selfie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selfie\"}, {\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 0.9999999971573743, \"rank\": 2.8425609674066624e-09, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 1329, \"end\": 1335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5224940632644775e-17, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 1361, \"end\": 1378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shirley_Robertson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shirley Robertson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shirley_Robertson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shirley_Robertson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What a brilliant execution.\", \"from\": 1450, \"to\": 1477, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In 2018, the British Sailing Federation started a scheme entitled Kite to Gold and I bet they are glad they did.\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1493, \"end\": 1500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8312164559229684, \"rank\": 0.12956999047903675, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have produced an Olympic champion at the first time of asking.\\\"\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1661, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Aldridge celebrated her success by jumping high into the air on her kiteboard, with former track cyclist and five-time Olympic gold medallist Laura Kenny exclaiming: \\\"I love the celebration.\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1853, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1805, \"end\": 1816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Kenny\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If we could have celebrated like that, that would have been class.\\\"\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1921, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not miss:Olympic gold medallist 'breaks up with his mum' as wild feud erupts in Paris  Do not miss:Two Olympic stars suffer gastrointestinal infections due to polluted River Seine  Do not miss:BBC Olympics commentator corrected after misgendering non-binary athlete in mask  Meanwhile, six-time Olympic gold medallist Sir Chris Hoy added: \\\"It's incredible.\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 2282, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2006, \"end\": 2011, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999977862899, \"rank\": 2.213741146923143e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/